-## Database Recommendations
-
-### Short-Term Storage (Last Hour): PostgreSQL
-
-**Why PostgreSQL (your current DB):**
-
-| Advantage | Details |
-|-----------|---------|
-| Γ£à Already set up | No new infrastructure needed |
-| Γ£à JSON support | `JSONField` for flexible message storage |
-| Γ£à Transactions | ACID compliance for reliable writes |
-| Γ£à Timestamp queries | Efficient filtering by time window |
-| Γ£à No additional cost | Uses existing database |
-
-**Implementation:**
-```python
-# Filter last hour of context
-from django.utils import timezone
-from datetime import timedelta
-
-one_hour_ago = timezone.now() - timedelta(hours=1)
-recent_messages = OrchestratorThread.objects.filter(
-    user=user,
-    updated_at__gte=one_hour_ago
-).order_by('-updated_at')
-```
-
-### Long-Term Storage (Vector DB): ChromaDB
-
-**Why ChromaDB (you already have it):**
-
-| Advantage | Details |
-|-----------|---------|
-| Γ£à Already integrated | Used for template search |
-| Γ£à Zero cost | Runs locally, no API costs |
-| Γ£à Semantic search | Find relevant past context |
-| Γ£à Python native | Easy Django integration |
-| Γ£à Scales well | Handles ~1M vectors efficiently |
-
-**Alternatives (for future scale):**
-
-| Database | When to Use | Cost |
-|----------|-------------|------|
-| **ChromaDB** | < 1M vectors, single server | Free |
-| **Qdrant** | > 1M vectors, high performance | Free (self-hosted) |
-| **Pinecone** | Managed, infinite scale | $70+/month |
-| **pgvector** | Want everything in PostgreSQL | Free |
-
-**Recommendation**: Start with **ChromaDB**. Migrate to Qdrant if you exceed 1M memories.
